{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ca0eb91b-39ef-4b5d-b399-729355b53a69","content":"In MSTest v4, the `TestMethod(string)` constructor parameter became a `[CallerMemberName]` parameter, so positional strings no longer set the display name. Use the **named property** `DisplayName` instead:\n\n```diff\n- [TestMethod(\"display name\")]\n+ [TestMethod(DisplayName = \"display name\")]\n```\n\nApplying the fix now:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Fi4fTRfkEjvVLg22aZss8e","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-99730dd78c444d92a2321eddd1d7e119/AuthTests.cs","old_str":"    [TestMethod(\"Verify user login works correctly\")]","new_str":"    [TestMethod(DisplayName = \"Verify user login works correctly\")]"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-99730dd78c444d92a2321eddd1d7e119/AuthTests.cs."},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Hr3sVm4ewXtZQNmiiaruVv","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-99730dd78c444d92a2321eddd1d7e119/AuthTests.cs","old_str":"    [TestMethodAttribute(\"Check admin privileges are enforced\")]","new_str":"    [TestMethod(DisplayName = \"Check admin privileges are enforced\")]"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-99730dd78c444d92a2321eddd1d7e119/AuthTests.cs."},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01EXTVWDYFd5KDH838dkmBKT","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-99730dd78c444d92a2321eddd1d7e119/AuthTests.cs","old_str":"    [TestMethod(\"Ensure logout clears session\")]","new_str":"    [TestMethod(DisplayName = \"Ensure logout clears session\")]"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-99730dd78c444d92a2321eddd1d7e119/AuthTests.cs."}],"interactionId":"f5b198b7-d1af-4c17-a6ad-dcc595e7d0fb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"In MSTest v4, the `TestMethodAttribute` constructor's string parameter now has `[CallerMemberName]`, so passing a display name positionally sets the caller member name instead. The fix is to use the named parameter `DisplayName = \"...\"` inste